<center>
<BODY LANG="en-US" TEXT="#000000" DIR="LTR">

<P ALIGN=CENTER><strong><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>MICROBIOLOGICAL
ASSAY</FONT></FONT></strong></P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><strong><FONT SIZE=3 STYLE="font-size: 13pt"><U><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>Method
  of Analysis No.: Micro/MoA 007</FONT></FONT></U></FONT></strong></P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><strong><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><I><U>Adapted
  from the USP 34 NF 29 2011 Vol. 1 Page 70 (Antibiotics – Microbial
  Assay)</U></I></FONT></FONT></strong></P>
<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="widows: 0; orphans: 0"><BR>
</P>
<TABLE WIDTH=709 CELLPADDING=7 CELLSPACING=0>
	<COL WIDTH=693>
	<TR>
		<TD WIDTH=693 HEIGHT=478 VALIGN=TOP STYLE="border: 1px solid #000000; padding: 0in 0.08in">
			<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="widows: 0; orphans: 0">&nbsp;</P>
			<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="widows: 0; orphans: 0"><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>Preparation
			of Standard solution:</B></FONT></FONT></P>
		  <P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0">
			<FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">Weigh
			accurately a weight of the standard equivalent to approx.
			100,000IU of Nystatin into a 25mL volumetric flask. Add a little
			dimethylformamide and sonicate for 10 minutes to dissolve. Allow
			to cool and then make up to volume with dimethylformamide. Dilute
			5mL of the resultant solution to 25mL using Buffer Solution pH 6.0
			that contains 5% v/v dimethylformamide. This gives solution </FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>S</B></FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>3
			</B></FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">i.e.</FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>
			</B></FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">Standard
			Stock Solution</FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>
			</B></FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">(~800
			IU/mL).</FONT></FONT></P>
			<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0">
			<FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">The
			standard solution should be prepared in </FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><U>duplicate</U></FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">
			(Std A &amp; B).</FONT></FONT><BR>
			</P>
			<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="widows: 0; orphans: 0"><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>Preparation
			of the Sample Solution:</B></FONT></FONT></P>
		  <P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0">
			<FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">Determine
			the relative density of the suspension. Weigh accurately a weight
			of the suspension equivalent to approx. 100,000 IU Nystatin to a
			25mL volumetric flask. Add a little dimethylformamide and sonicate
			for 10 minutes to dissolve. Allow to cool and then make up to
			volume with dimethylformamide. Take 5mL of this solution into a
			25mL volumetric flask and top up with Buffer Solution pH 6.0 that
			contains 5% v/v dimethylformamide. This gives solution </FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>T</B></FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>3
			</B></FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">i.e.</FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>
			</B></FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">Sample
			Stock Solution (~800 IU/mL).</FONT></FONT></P>
			<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0">
			<FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">The
			sample solution should be prepared in </FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><U>triplicate</U></FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">
			(Test A, B, &amp; C).</FONT></FONT></P>
			<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="widows: 0; orphans: 0"><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>Preparation
			of the test solutions:</B></FONT></FONT></P>
			<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0">
			<FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">Dilute
			both Solutions </FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>S</B></FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>3</B></FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">
			and </FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>T</B></FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>3
			</B></FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">as
			follows:</FONT></FONT></P>
			<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0">
			<FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">Dilute
			5mL to 10mL using </FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">Buffer
			Solution pH 6.0 which contains 5% v/v dimethylformamide; this
			gives solutions </FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>S</B></FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>2</B></FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">
			and </FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>T</B></FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>2</B></FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">
			respectively.</FONT></FONT></P>
			<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0">
			<FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">From
			the S</FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">2</FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">
			and T</FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">2</FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">
			solution take 5mL and dilute to 10mL with Buffer Solution pH 6.0
			which contains 5% v/v dimethylformamide; this yields solutions </FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>S</B></FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>1</B></FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">
			and </FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>T</B></FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>1</B></FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">
			respectively.</FONT></FONT></P>
			<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="widows: 0; orphans: 0"><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>Preparation
			of Innoculum:</B></FONT></FONT></P>
			<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0">
			<FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">From
			a recently grown slant of </FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><I>Sacharomyces
			cerevisiae, </I></FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">subculture
			onto a plate of Sabouraud Agar and incubate at 35</FONT></FONT><SUP><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">
			o </FONT></FONT></SUP><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">C</FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><I>
			</I></FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">for
			5 days or until sufficient growth is attained. Harvest the growth
			using sterile water or normal saline into a test-tube or sterile
			bottle.</FONT></FONT></P>
			<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="widows: 0; orphans: 0"><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>Preparation
		    of the Media:</B></FONT></FONT></P>
			<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0">
			<FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">Weigh
			Sabouraud Agar and reconstitute with water as prescribed by the
			manufacturer to give a volume sufficient for analysis. Autoclave
			at 121</FONT></FONT><SUP><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">o
			</FONT></FONT></SUP><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">C
			for 15minutes. Allow cooling to about 50</FONT></FONT><SUP><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">
			o </FONT></FONT></SUP><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">C
			before adding the innoculum (approx. 4mL of the suspension of
			</FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><I>Sacharomyces
			cerevisiae</I></FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">
			harvested). Swirl the bottle to mix the innoculum while avoiding
			introduction of air bubbles. </FONT></FONT>
			</P>
			<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0">
			<BR>
			<FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>Preparation
			of the plates: </B></FONT></FONT>			</P>
			<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0">
			<FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">Measure
			out 25mL of the inoculated media using a measuring cylinder into
			each of the plates to be used for the assay. Let the plate settle
			for about 1hour. When the media has hardened enough, make 6
			cylindrical wells using the borer and the template guide in each
			plate. Label the wells with the solutions to be put into each
			well, in the following order: T</FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">2</FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">-T</FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">3</FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">-T</FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">1</FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">-
			S</FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">3</FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">-S</FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">1</FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">-
			S</FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">2</FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">.
			</FONT></FONT>
			</P>
			<P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0">
			<FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">Each
			assay uses a total of 18 plates, thus:</FONT></FONT></P>
			<UL>
			<LI>
			  <P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 2; orphans: 2">
				<FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">3
			  plates having Std A and Test A test solutions,</FONT></FONT></P>
			  <P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 2; orphans: 2"><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">3
		      plates having Std A and Test B test solutions,</FONT></FONT> </P>                            
			  <LI>
				  <P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 2; orphans: 2"> <FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">3
				      plates having Std A and Test C test solutions,</FONT></FONT></P>
		      <LI>
				      <P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 2; orphans: 2"> <FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">3
				        plates having Std B and Test A test solutions,</FONT></FONT></P>
		      <LI>
				        <P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 2; orphans: 2"> <FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">3
				          plates having Std B and Test B test solutions,</FONT></FONT></P>
	          <LI>
				          <P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 2; orphans: 2"> <FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">3
				            plates having Std B and Test C test solutions.</FONT></FONT></P>
          </UL>
            <P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0"> <BR>
              <FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>Performing
          the Test:</B></FONT></FONT></P>
            <P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0"> <FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">Using
              the 50-μL-micropipette transfer 50 μL of each of the Solutions
              into the appropriately labeled wells. After completion, allow the
              petri dishes to stand for 2 hours before incubating them at 35</FONT></FONT><SUP><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"> o </FONT></FONT></SUP><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">C
                for about 18-24 hours.</FONT></FONT></P>
          <P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0"> <FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">Read
              the diameters of the zones of inhibition using a caliper and
              record them in the table.</FONT></FONT></P>
            <P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0"><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><B>Calculations: </B></FONT></FONT> </P>
            <P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0"> <FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">Calculate
              the amount of Nystatin in each of the samples using the formulae
              below:</FONT></FONT></P>
            <P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0"> <BR>
              <FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">E
              = ¼[(S</SPAN></FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">3</SPAN></FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">+T</SPAN></FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">3</SPAN></FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">)-(S</SPAN></FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">1</SPAN></FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">+
            T</SPAN></FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">1</SPAN></FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">)]</SPAN></FONT></FONT></P>
            <P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0"> <FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">F
              = </SPAN></FONT></FONT><SUP><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">1</SPAN></FONT></FONT></SUP><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">/</SPAN></FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">3</SPAN></FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">[(T</SPAN></FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">3</SPAN></FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">+
                T</SPAN></FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">2</SPAN></FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">+
                  T</SPAN></FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">1</SPAN></FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">)-(S</SPAN></FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">3</SPAN></FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">+
                    S</SPAN></FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">2</SPAN></FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">+
                      S</SPAN></FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">1</SPAN></FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><SPAN LANG="de-DE">)] </SPAN></FONT></FONT> </P>
            <P LANG="de-DE" CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0"> <FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">b
              = E/log Dose Ratio </FONT></FONT></P>
            <P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0"> <FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">m
              = F/b </FONT></FONT> </P>
            <P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0"> <FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">Antilog
              m = Factor</FONT></FONT></P>
            <P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0"> <FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">%
              Label Claim = Factor X  [</FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"><U>S
                t d]</U></FONT></FONT><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"> X 100</FONT></FONT></P>
            <P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0"> <FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt"> [Smp]</FONT></FONT></P>
            <P CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="font-weight: normal; widows: 0; orphans: 0"> <FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">Where		S</FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">3</FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">,
              S</FONT></FONT><SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">2</FONT></FONT></SUB><FONT FACE="Book Antiqua, serif"><FONT SIZE=2 STYLE="font-size: 11pt">,
